{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880807261,"sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","part":{"id":"prt_d7abe9f5e001zNclCn44Yhs1tN","messageID":"msg_d7abe96270019gKKcrJo0y7po9","sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_64593f3341bb477281257957","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n9: \n10: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n11: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n12: - [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n13: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n14: \n15: ## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n16: \n17: - [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n18: - [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n19: - [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n20: - [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple\n21: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_id` raises `ValueError`\n22: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_endpoint` raises `ValueError`\n23: \n24: ## T-3: InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation\n25: \n26: - [ ] Implement `_direct_http_invocation(endpoint: str, payload: Dict, headers: Dict[str, str], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict`\n27: - [ ] POST JSON to `{endpoint}` using `httpx` (sync client)\n28: - [ ] Parse JSON response; return parsed dict\n29: - [ ] On non-2xx status, raise exception with status code and response body\n30: - [ ] Write test: successful POST returns parsed JSON response\n31: - [ ] Write test: non-2xx response raises exception with status code\n32: - [ ] Write test: custom headers are included in request\n33: \n34: ## T-4: InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n35: \n36: - [ ] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path) -> Dict`\n37: - [ ] Load metadata; if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n38: - [ ] If `metadata.session_id` exists, inject header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id`\n39: - [ ] POST JSON to rewritten endpoint; return parsed response\n40: - [ ] Write test: endpoint rewriting when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n41: - [ ] Write test: session header injection when `session_id` present\n42: - [ ] Write test: no rewriting when deployment type is not `AgentRuntime`\n43: - [ ] Write test: no session header when `session_id` is absent\n44: \n45: ## T-5: InvokeRuntime.invoke (orchestration)\n46: \n47: - [ ] Implement `invoke(workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict, headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict`\n48: - [ ] Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` → get metadata, agent_id, endpoint\n49: - [ ] If `self.provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n50: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n51: - [ ] Return the response\n52: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n53: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_direct_http_invocation`\n54: \n55: ## T-6: invoke CLI command entry point\n56: \n57: - [ ] Add `invoke()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n58: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `payload` (`--payload`, default `\"{}\"`), `header_list` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n59: - [ ] Parse `--payload` as JSON; on invalid JSON, print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red, exit code `1`\n60: - [ ] Parse `--header` entries: split on first `:`, strip key/value; on missing `:`, print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red, exit code `1`\n61: - [ ] Merge multiple headers into single `Dict[str, str]`\n62: - [ ] Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` within error handler\n63: - [ ] On success, print response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n64: - [ ] On error, use `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n65: - [ ] Write test: successful invoke prints response, exit 0\n66: - [ ] Write test: invalid JSON payload → error message, exit 1\n67: - [ ] Write test: invalid header format → error message, exit 1\n68: - [ ] Write test: multiple headers merged correctly\n69: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n70: - [ ] Write test: quiet error prints message only, exit 1\n71: \n72: ## T-7: StatusRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n73: \n74: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class\n75: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n76: - [ ] Add `StatusRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n77: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly\n78: \n79: ## T-8: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status\n80: \n81: - [ ] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n82: - [ ] Use `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name)` to fetch CR\n83: - [ ] If CR exists and has `status` field → return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n84: - [ ] If CR exists but no `status` field → return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n85: - [ ] If CR not found → return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n86: - [ ] Write test: CR exists with status → returns status + endpoint\n87: - [ ] Write test: CR exists without status → returns `created_no_status`\n88: - [ ] Write test: CR not found → returns `not_found_in_k8s`\n89: \n90: ## T-9: StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status\n91: \n92: - [ ] Implement `_get_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n93: - [ ] Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` (see T-11)\n94: - [ ] Return the result dict\n95: - [ ] Write test: calls `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and returns result\n96: \n97: ## T-10: StatusRuntime.get_status (orchestration)\n98: \n99: - [ ] Implement `get_status(workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict`\n100: - [ ] Load metadata from workspace via `MetadataService`\n101: - [ ] If no `agent_id` → return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n102: - [ ] If `provider == \"agentcube\"` (or default), call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n103: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n104: - [ ] Return the status dict\n105: - [ ] Write test: no `agent_id` → returns `not_published`\n106: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n107: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_get_k8s_status`\n108: \n109: ## T-11: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\n110: \n111: - [ ] Add `get_agent_status(agent_name: str) -> Dict` to `KubernetesProvider`\n112: - [ ] Query deployment status via `AppsV1Api.read_namespaced_deployment_status`\n113: - [ ] Query pod status via `CoreV1Api.list_namespaced_pod` with label selector\n114: - [ ] Return dict with deployment status, pod statuses, endpoint info\n115: - [ ] On 404, return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n116: - [ ] Write test: deployment found with ready pods → returns status\n117: - [ ] Write test: deployment not found → returns `not_found`\n118: \n119: ## T-12: status CLI command entry point\n120: \n121: - [ ] Add `status()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n122: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n123: - [ ] Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n124: - [ ] If status == `\"not_published\"` → print guidance to run `publish` first, exit code `1`\n125: - [ ] If status == `\"error\"` → print error details, exit code `1`\n126: - [ ] Otherwise, render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n127: - [ ] On exception, use `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n128: - [ ] Write test: not_published → guidance message, exit 1\n129: - [ ] Write test: error status → error details, exit 1\n130: - [ ] Write test: valid status → Rich Table rendered with required fields\n131: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n132: \n133: ## T-13: Provider validation (cross-cutting)\n134: \n135: - [ ] Add provider validation to both `invoke` and `status` commands: reject values other than `\"agentcube\"` / `\"k8s\"`\n136: - [ ] Write test: invalid provider → error message, exit 1\n137: \n138: ## T-14: Integration tests\n139: \n140: - [ ] Write integration test: full invoke flow with mocked HTTP (mock `httpx.Client`)\n141: - [ ] Write integration test: full status flow with mocked K8s (mock `AgentCubeProvider` / `KubernetesProvider`)\n142: - [ ] Write integration test: invoke with session header end-to-end (mocked)\n143: \n144: ## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n145: \n146: - [ ] `ruff check agentcube/` — no violations\n147: - [ ] `mypy agentcube/` — no type errors\n148: - [ ] `pytest tests/ -v` — all pass\n149: - [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Dependency Graph\n154: \n155: ```\n156: T-1  ──┬── T-2 ──┬── T-5 ── T-6\n157:        │          │\n158:        │          └── T-4 ──┘\n159:        │\n160:        └── T-3 ──┘\n161: \n162: T-7  ──┬── T-8 ──┬── T-10 ── T-12\n163:        │          │\n164:        └── T-9 ──┘  (T-9 depends on T-11)\n165: \n166: T-11 ── T-9\n167: \n168: T-13 ── (T-6, T-12)\n169: \n170: T-14 ── (T-6, T-12)\n171: \n172: T-15 ── (all above)\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## Parallelizable Groups\n176: \n177: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n178: |-------|-------|---------------|\n179: | G1 | T-1, T-7 | None |\n180: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11 | T-1 |\n181: | G3 | T-4, T-8, T-9 | T-2, T-11 |\n182: | G4 | T-5, T-10 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-8, T-9 |\n183: | G5 | T-6, T-12, T-13 | T-5, T-10 |\n184: | G6 | T-14 | T-6, T-12 |\n185: | G7 | T-15 | All above |\n\n(End of file - total 185 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n- [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n\n## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n- [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n- [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n- [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775880807246,"end":1775880807259}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880808473,"sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","part":{"id":"prt_d7abea3de001d4YkuY2EjngW3O","messageID":"msg_d7abe96270019gKKcrJo0y7po9","sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7f931312887c4bf0a1e79c98","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\nclientset/\ninformers/\nlisters/\n\n(3 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"clientset/\ninformers/\nlisters/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go","time":{"start":1775880808469,"end":1775880808472}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880809637,"sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","part":{"id":"prt_d7abea8a4001lCBpZXcKWk1q3c","messageID":"msg_d7abe96270019gKKcrJo0y7po9","sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d1c2b80850dd482785b90559","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n8: \n9: 1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n10: 2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n11: 3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n12: 4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n13: 5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 System Context\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                         User Application                            │\n20: │  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │\n21: │  │   CodeInterpreterClient   │   │    AgentRuntimeClient       │   │\n22: │  │   (High-level facade)     │   │    (High-level facade)      │   │\n23: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n24: │              │                                   │                   │\n25: │  ┌───────────▼───────────────┐   ┌──────────────▼──────────────┐   │\n26: │  │   ControlPlaneClient      │   │   CodeInterpreterDataPlane  │   │\n27: │  │   (Workload Manager)      │   │   AgentRuntimeDataPlane     │   │\n28: │  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n29: └──────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────┘\n30:                │                                  │\n31:                ▼                                  ▼\n32:     ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────┐\n33:     │  Workload Manager    │          │  Router (Data Plane)   │\n34:     │  (Control Plane API) │          │  /v1/namespaces/...    │\n35:     └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────┘\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n39: \n40: - **No single `Configuration` class**: Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across client constructors.\n41: - **Context manager support**: All clients support `with` statement for proper resource cleanup.\n42: - **Session header convention**: Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router requests.\n43: - **Timeout safety**: Read timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n44: - **Connection pooling**: `HTTPAdapter` with configurable pool size for all HTTP sessions.\n45: \n46: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n47: \n48: ```\n49: sdk-python/\n50: ├── pyproject.toml                          # Package metadata, dependencies\n51: ├── agentcube/\n52: │   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n53: │   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient (high-level facade)\n54: │   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient (high-level facade)\n55: │   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n56: │   ├── clients/\n57: │   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports: ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n58: │   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager HTTP)\n59: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n60: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n61: │   └── utils/\n62: │       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n63: │       ├── http.py                         # create_session()\n64: │       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file()\n65: │       └── log.py                          # get_logger()\n66: ├── examples/\n67: │   ├── basic_usage.py\n68: │   └── agent_runtime_usage.py\n69: ├── scripts/\n70: │   └── e2e_picod_test.py\n71: └── tests/\n72:     ├── test_code_interpreter.py\n73:     ├── test_agent_runtime.py\n74:     ├── test_control_plane.py\n75:     ├── test_data_plane.py\n76:     └── test_exceptions.py\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n80: \n81: ```toml\n82: dependencies = [\n83:     \"requests\",\n84:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n85:     \"cryptography\",\n86: ]\n87: \n88: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n89: \n90: [build-system]\n91: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n92: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n93: \n94: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n95: where = [\".\"]\n96: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n97: namespaces = false\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 2. Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n105: \n106: ```\n107: Exception\n108: └── AgentCubeError (base for all SDK exceptions)\n109:     ├── CommandExecutionError (non-zero exit code from remote command)\n110:     │   Attributes: exit_code, stderr, command\n111:     │   Message: \"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n112:     ├── SessionError (session creation/management failures)\n113:     └── DataPlaneError (data plane operation failures)\n114: ```\n115: \n116: **Design Notes:**\n117: - `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules.\n118: - Core clients raise `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n119: \n120: ### 2.2 Client Instance State\n121: \n122: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n123: | Field | Type | Source |\n124: |-------|------|--------|\n125: | `name` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n126: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n127: | `ttl` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `3600`) |\n128: | `verbose` | `bool` | Constructor arg (default: `False`) |\n129: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n130: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n131: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n132: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Arg or from `create_session()` |\n133: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Created in `_init_data_plane()` |\n134: \n135: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n136: | Field | Type | Source |\n137: |-------|------|--------|\n138: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n139: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n140: | `timeout` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `120`) |\n141: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Constructor arg (default: `5.0`) |\n142: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n143: | `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n144: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | From `bootstrap_session_id()` |\n145: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n146: \n147: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n148: | Field | Type | Source |\n149: |-------|------|--------|\n150: | `base_url` | `str` | Arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n151: | `auth_token` | `str` | Arg or SA token file |\n152: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n153: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n154: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n155: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n156: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n157: \n158: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n159: | Field | Type | Source |\n160: |-------|------|--------|\n161: | `session_id` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n162: | `base_url` | `str` | Explicit arg or `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n163: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n164: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n165: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n166: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n167: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n168: \n169: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n170: | Field | Type | Source |\n171: |-------|------|--------|\n172: | `SESSION_HEADER` | `str` | Class constant: `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n173: | `router_url` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n174: | `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n175: | `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n176: | `base_url` | `str` | `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n177: | `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n178: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n179: | `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n180: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n181: | `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 3. API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### 3.1 HTTP Utilities\n188: \n189: #### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n190: \n191: ```python\n192: def create_session(\n193:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n194:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n195: ) -> requests.Session:\n196:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n197: ```\n198: \n199: - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://`\n200: - Default pool: 10 connections, max size 10\n201: \n202: #### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n206:     \"\"\"Read and strip token from file. Returns '' on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: #### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n213:     \"\"\"Create a configured logger.\"\"\"\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### 3.2 Control Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n217: \n218: #### Constructor Resolution\n219: \n220: | Setting | Primary | Fallback |\n221: |---------|---------|----------|\n222: | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n223: | `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n224: \n225: #### HTTP Endpoints\n226: \n227: | Method | Path | Body | Response | Notes |\n228: |--------|------|------|----------|-------|\n229: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"...\"}}` | Returns `sessionId` |\n230: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 2xx success, 404 = success | 404 treated as success |\n231: \n232: #### Methods\n233: \n234: ```python\n235: class ControlPlaneClient:\n236:     def __init__(\n237:         self,\n238:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n239:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n240:         timeout: int = 120,\n241:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n242:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n243:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n244:     )\n245: \n246:     def create_session(\n247:         self,\n248:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n249:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n250:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n251:         ttl: int = 3600,\n252:     ) -> str:\n253:         \"\"\"Create session, return session_id. Raise ValueError if sessionId absent.\"\"\"\n254: \n255:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n256:         \"\"\"Delete session. Return True on success or 404, False on other failures.\"\"\"\n257: \n258:     def close(self) -> None:\n259:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n260: ```\n261: \n262: **Headers:**\n263: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n264: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n265: \n266: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple on each request\n267: \n268: ### 3.3 Code Interpreter Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n269: \n270: #### Base URL Construction\n271: \n272: ```python\n273: if base_url is None:\n274:     base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n275:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: #### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n279: \n280: | Method | Path | Body | Notes |\n281: |--------|------|------|-------|\n282: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = `timeout_value + 2.0` |\n283: | `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | JSON body |\n284: | `POST` | `api/files` | multipart `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload |\n285: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`, `stream=True` |\n286: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` | List files |\n287: \n288: #### Methods\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n292:     def __init__(\n293:         self,\n294:         session_id: str,\n295:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n296:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n297:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n298:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n299:         timeout: int = 120,\n300:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n301:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n302:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n303:     )\n304: \n305:     def _request(\n306:         self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs\n307:     ) -> requests.Response:\n308:         \"\"\"Internal HTTP request helper. Sets Content-Type: application/json when body is set.\"\"\"\n309: \n310:     def execute_command(\n311:         self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None\n312:     ) -> str:\n313:         \"\"\"Execute command. Raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n314: \n315:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n316:         \"\"\"Execute code. Python variants write timestamped .py file first.\"\"\"\n317: \n318:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n319:         \"\"\"Write file content (base64 encoded).\"\"\"\n320: \n321:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n322:         \"\"\"Upload file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n323: \n324:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n325:         \"\"\"Download file with streaming.\"\"\"\n326: \n327:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n328:         \"\"\"List files at path.\"\"\"\n329: \n330:     def close(self) -> None:\n331:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Headers:**\n335: - Default session: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` (when `body` is set in `_request`)\n337: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n338: \n339: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n340: \n341: #### `execute_command` Timeout Logic\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n345: # PicoD timeout string\n346: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"\n347: # Read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n348: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\n349: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n350: ```\n351: \n352: #### `run_code` Python Execution Path\n353: \n354: - Languages: `python`, `py`, `python3`\n355: - Writes timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n356: - Executes `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n357: \n358: ### 3.4 Agent Runtime Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n359: \n360: #### Base URL Construction\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n364: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n365: ```\n366: \n367: #### HTTP Endpoints\n368: \n369: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n370: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n371: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers only | — |\n372: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n373: \n374: #### Methods\n375: \n376: ```python\n377: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n378:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n379: \n380:     def __init__(\n381:         self,\n382:         router_url: str,\n383:         namespace: str,\n384:         agent_name: str,\n385:         timeout: int = 120,\n386:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n387:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n388:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n389:     )\n390: \n391:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n392:         \"\"\"GET base_url, read x-agentcube-session-id header. Raise ValueError if missing.\"\"\"\n393: \n394:     def invoke(\n395:         self,\n396:         session_id: str,\n397:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n398:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n399:     ) -> requests.Response:\n400:         \"\"\"POST JSON payload with session header.\"\"\"\n401: \n402:     def close(self) -> None:\n403:         \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n404: ```\n405: \n406: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` defaults to `self.timeout` (120)\n407: \n408: ### 3.5 High-Level Facades\n409: \n410: #### `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n411: \n412: ```python\n413: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n414:     def __init__(\n415:         self,\n416:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n417:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n418:         ttl: int = 3600,\n419:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n420:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n421:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n422:         verbose: bool = False,\n423:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n424:     )\n425: \n426:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n427:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n428:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n429:     def stop(self) -> None\n430:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n431:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n432:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n433:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n434:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n435:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n436: ```\n437: \n438: **Lifecycle:**\n439: 1. If `session_id` provided: reuse it, skip control plane\n440: 2. If `session_id` not provided: call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, then `_init_data_plane()`\n441: 3. On `_init_data_plane()` failure: log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n442: \n443: #### `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n444: \n445: ```python\n446: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n447:     def __init__(\n448:         self,\n449:         agent_name: str,\n450:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n451:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n452:         verbose: bool = False,\n453:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n454:         timeout: int = 120,\n455:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n456:     )\n457: \n458:     def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n459:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n460:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n461:     def close(self) -> None\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **Lifecycle:**\n465: 1. If `session_id` not provided: call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()`\n466: 2. `invoke()` requires `session_id` to be set, else `ValueError`\n467: \n468: ### 3.6 Public Package Surface\n469: \n470: ```python\n471: # agentcube/__init__.py\n472: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n473: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n474: \n475: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n476: ```\n477: \n478: ```python\n479: # agentcube/clients/__init__.py\n480: __all__ = [\n481:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n482:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n483:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n484: ]\n485: ```\n486: \n487: **Note:** Only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` are exported from the root package. Data plane and control plane clients are internal implementation details accessible via `agentcube.clients.*`.\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## 4. Configuration Summary\n492: \n493: | Component | Resolved Settings |\n494: |-----------|-------------------|\n495: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n496: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n497: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n498: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n499: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n500: \n501: ---\n502: \n503: ## 5. Error Handling\n504: \n505: ### 5.1 Error Classification\n506: \n507: | Scenario | Exception | Source |\n508: |----------|-----------|--------|\n509: | Router URL missing | `ValueError` | `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n510: | Session ID bootstrap missing header | `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` |\n511: | Invoke without session | `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` |\n512: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` |\n513: | Create session missing sessionId | `ValueError` | `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` |\n514: | Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (not exception) | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n515: | Delete session other failure | Logs, returns `False` | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n516: | Data plane init failure | Logs warning, cleanup, re-raise | `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()` |\n517: | HTTP errors | `requests.HTTPError` or similar | `requests` library |\n518: \n519: ### 5.2 Timeout Strategy\n520: \n521: | Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout | Notes |\n522: |-----------|-----------------|--------------|-------|\n523: | Control Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n524: | Code Interpreter Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n525: | `execute_command` | `5.0s` | `timeout_value + 2.0s` | Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout |\n526: | Agent Runtime Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n527: \n528: **Timeout tuple format:** `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` passed to `requests`\n529: \n530: ### 5.3 Exception Flow\n531: \n532: ```\n533: ValueError                    ← Configuration errors, missing session, missing headers\n534: CommandExecutionError         ← Non-zero exit code from remote command\n535: requests.RequestException     ← HTTP failures (connection errors, timeouts)\n536: requests.HTTPError            ← Non-2xx responses (if raised)\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## 6. Implementation Notes\n542: \n543: ### 6.1 Session Header Consistency\n544: \n545: All Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n546: \n547: - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n548: - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`, set explicitly on each `POST` request\n549: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` set explicitly on the request (no JSON Content-Type)\n550: \n551: ### 6.2 Timeout Tuple Logic\n552: \n553: For `execute_command`:\n554: \n555: ```python\n556: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n557: timeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"  # PicoD timeout string\n558: read_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0      # Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\n559: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n560: ```\n561: \n562: For `invoke`:\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: effective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n566: request_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ### 6.3 Context Manager Pattern\n570: \n571: ```python\n572: # Code Interpreter\n573: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n574:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n575:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n576: ) as client:\n577:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n578: \n579: # Agent Runtime\n580: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n581:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n582:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n583: ) as client:\n584:     response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\"})\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### 6.4 Data Plane Init Failure Cleanup\n588: \n589: ```python\n590: def _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n591:     try:\n592:         self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n593:             session_id=self.session_id,\n594:             router_url=self.router_url,\n595:             namespace=self.namespace,\n596:             cr_name=self.name,\n597:         )\n598:     except Exception:\n599:         self.logger.warning(\"Data plane init failed, cleaning up session %s\", self.session_id)\n600:         self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n601:         self.session_id = None\n602:         raise\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ---\n606: \n607: ## 7. Testing Strategy\n608: \n609: ### 7.1 Test Categories\n610: \n611: | Category | Scope | Tools |\n612: |----------|-------|-------|\n613: | Unit tests | Individual client methods, exception handling | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` |\n614: | Integration tests | HTTP endpoint contracts (mocked server) | `pytest`, `responses` or `httpretty` |\n615: | E2E tests | Full lifecycle against PicoD | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n616: \n617: ### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n618: \n619: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n620: \n621: | Test Name | Description |\n622: |-----------|-------------|\n623: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `stop()` |\n624: | `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | Data plane init failure cleans up session and re-raises |\n625: | `test_router_url_required` | Router URL required (arg or env) |\n626: | `test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` | `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit |\n627: | `test_run_code_python_writes_file` | `run_code` with Python writes timestamped file and executes |\n628: | `test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane` | Reuse of provided `session_id` skips control plane |\n629: \n630: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n631: \n632: | Test Name | Description |\n633: |-----------|-------------|\n634: | `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `close()` |\n635: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID reads header, raises `ValueError` if missing |\n636: | `test_invoke_without_session` | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` |\n637: | `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` | Invoke timeout tuple construction |\n638: \n639: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n640: \n641: | Test Name | Description |\n642: |-----------|-------------|\n643: | `test_create_session_returns_session_id` | Create session returns `sessionId`, raises `ValueError` if absent |\n644: | `test_delete_session_404_returns_true` | Delete session 404 returns `True` |\n645: | `test_delete_session_failure_returns_false` | Delete session other failure returns `False` |\n646: | `test_auth_token_from_sa_file` | Auth token from SA file fallback |\n647: | `test_base_url_from_env` | Base URL from env fallback |\n648: \n649: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n650: \n651: | Test Name | Description |\n652: |-----------|-------------|\n653: | `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer` | Execute command timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) |\n654: | `test_write_file_base64` | Write file base64 encoding |\n655: | `test_upload_file_multipart_session_header` | Upload file multipart with session header |\n656: | `test_download_file_streaming` | Download file streaming |\n657: | `test_list_files_query_parameter` | List files query parameter |\n658: \n659: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n660: \n661: | Test Name | Description |\n662: |-----------|-------------|\n663: | `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n664: | `test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises` | Bootstrap missing header raises `ValueError` |\n665: | `test_invoke_with_session_header` | Invoke POST with session header and JSON body |\n666: \n667: #### Exceptions\n668: \n669: | Test Name | Description |\n670: |-----------|-------------|\n671: | `test_command_execution_error_attributes` | `CommandExecutionError` attributes and message format |\n672: | `test_exception_hierarchy` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError` base) |\n673: | `test_session_error_data_plane_error_defined` | `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core |\n674: \n675: ### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n676: \n677: - Mock `requests.Session` and its methods (`get`, `post`, `delete`)\n678: - Mock `read_token_from_file` for auth token tests\n679: - Mock environment variables with `monkeypatch`\n680: - Use `responses` library for HTTP endpoint contract tests\n681: \n682: ### 7.4 Example Test Structure\n683: \n684: ```python\n685: # tests/test_code_interpreter.py\n686: class TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n687:     def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client): ...\n688:     def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client): ...\n689:     def test_router_url_required(self): ...\n690:     def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n691:     def test_run_code_python_writes_file(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n692:     def test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane(self): ...\n693: \n694: # tests/test_control_plane.py\n695: class TestControlPlaneClient:\n696:     def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n697:     def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n698:     def test_delete_session_404_returns_true(self, mock_session): ...\n699:     def test_delete_session_failure_returns_false(self, mock_session): ...\n700:     def test_auth_token_from_sa_file(self, mock_read_token): ...\n701:     def test_base_url_from_env(self, monkeypatch): ...\n702: \n703: # tests/test_data_plane.py\n704: class TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n705:     def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self, mock_session): ...\n706:     def test_write_file_base64(self, mock_session): ...\n707:     def test_upload_file_multipart_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n708: \n709: class TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n710:     def test_bootstrap_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n711:     def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n712:     def test_invoke_with_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## 8. Usage Examples\n718: \n719: ### 8.1 Code Interpreter — Basic Usage\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n723: \n724: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n725:     name=\"my-interpreter\",\n726:     namespace=\"default\",\n727:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n728: ) as client:\n729:     # Execute shell command\n730:     result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n731:     print(result)\n732: \n733:     # Run Python code\n734:     result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\n735:     print(result)\n736: \n737:     # Write file\n738:     client.write_file(\"content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n739: \n740:     # List files\n741:     files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n742:     print(files)\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ### 8.2 Code Interpreter — Reuse Session\n746: \n747: ```python\n748: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n749: \n750: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n751:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n752:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n753: )\n754: \n755: try:\n756:     result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\n757: finally:\n758:     client.stop()\n759: ```\n760: \n761: ### 8.3 Agent Runtime — Basic Usage\n762: \n763: ```python\n764: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n765: \n766: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n767:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n768:     namespace=\"production\",\n769:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n770: ) as client:\n771:     response = client.invoke({\n772:         \"action\": \"process\",\n773:         \"data\": {\"input\": \"hello world\"}\n774:     })\n775:     print(response)\n776: ```\n777: \n778: ### 8.4 Agent Runtime — Custom Timeout\n779: \n780: ```python\n781: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n782: \n783: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n784:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n785:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n786:     timeout=300,  # 5 minute read timeout\n787: ) as client:\n788:     response = client.invoke(\n789:         {\"action\": \"long_running_task\"},\n790:         timeout=600  # Override to 10 minutes for this call\n791:     )\n792: ```\n\n(End of file - total 792 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n\n1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User Application                            │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775880809621,"end":1775880809635}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880811165,"sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","part":{"id":"prt_d7abead23001Qz1S82czVryZLN","messageID":"msg_d7abe96270019gKKcrJo0y7po9","sessionID":"ses_2854178afffe40mg2XimqIneGs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c3b00d99853948699957cae6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## HTTP Session Factory\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: create_session\n19: The system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: default pool parameters\n22: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called with no arguments\n23: - **WHEN** the session is created\n24: - **THEN** `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` SHALL be mounted for both `http://` and `https://` prefixes\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: custom pool parameters\n27: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n28: - **WHEN** the session is created\n29: - **THEN** both adapters SHALL use the provided pool parameters\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## ControlPlaneClient\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient constructor\n36: The system SHALL initialize `ControlPlaneClient` with URL resolution from arguments or environment, and auth token resolution from arguments or ServiceAccount file.\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: base URL from argument\n39: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\")`\n40: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n41: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm:8080\"`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: base URL from environment\n44: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` is `None` and env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set to `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n45: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n46: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://wm-env:9090\"`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: auth token from argument\n49: - **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n50: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n51: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: auth token from ServiceAccount file\n54: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` or empty and file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `\"sa-token\\n\"`\n55: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n56: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be `\"Bearer sa-token\"`\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: auth token file not found\n59: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is `None` and the ServiceAccount token file does not exist\n60: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n61: - **THEN** `read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"` and `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be set\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: empty token skips Authorization header\n64: - **GIVEN** resolved token is empty string\n65: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n66: - **THEN** `session.headers` SHALL NOT contain `Authorization`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: default Content-Type header\n69: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n70: - **WHEN** session headers are inspected\n71: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"Content-Type\"]` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: default timeout parameters\n74: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is called with no timeout arguments\n75: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n76: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.create_session\n79: The system SHALL POST to the Workload Manager to create a Code Interpreter session and return the session ID.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: successful session creation\n82: - **GIVEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"key\": \"val\"})`\n83: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n84: - **THEN** `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"key\": \"val\"}}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: response contains sessionId\n87: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}}`\n88: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n89: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: response missing sessionId\n92: - **GIVEN** the server returns `{\"data\": {}}`\n93: - **WHEN** the response is parsed\n94: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `ValueError`\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: request timeout tuple\n97: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n98: - **WHEN** any request is sent\n99: - **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session\n102: The system SHALL DELETE a session and treat 404 as success.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: successful deletion\n105: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 200\n106: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n107: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: 404 treated as success\n110: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent\")` returns HTTP 404\n111: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n112: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: other error logged and returns False\n115: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"sess-1\")` returns HTTP 500\n116: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n117: - **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: ControlPlaneClient.close\n120: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: close releases session\n123: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.close()` is called\n124: - **WHEN** the method executes\n125: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructor\n132: The system SHALL initialize the data plane client with base URL derived from router URL or explicit `base_url`.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: base URL from router URL\n135: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\")`\n136: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n137: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"`\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: base URL explicit override\n140: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(base_url=\"http://custom/url/\")`\n141: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n142: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://custom/url/\"` and router/namespace/cr_name SHALL be ignored for URL construction\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: session header set\n145: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n146: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n147: - **THEN** `session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"]` SHALL be `\"sess-1\"`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: default timeouts\n150: - **GIVEN** no timeout arguments provided\n151: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n152: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: _request method\n155: The system SHALL send HTTP requests with appropriate headers based on whether a body is present.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: JSON body request\n158: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"POST\", \"api/execute\", body=b'{\"cmd\": \"ls\"}')`\n159: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n160: - **THEN** `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set on the request and URL SHALL be `urljoin(self.base_url, \"api/execute\")`\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: request without body\n163: - **GIVEN** `_request(\"GET\", \"api/files\")`\n164: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n165: - **THEN** no `Content-Type` override SHALL be set (session defaults apply)\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: execute_command\n168: The system SHALL POST to `api/execute` with command and timeout, adding a 2-second buffer to read timeout.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: command with explicit timeout\n171: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"sleep 10\", timeout=10.0)`\n172: - **WHEN** the request is built\n173: - **THEN** HTTP read timeout SHALL be `12.0` (`timeout + 2.0`) and body SHALL contain `{\"command\": [\"sleep 10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: command with default timeout\n176: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=None)` and `self.timeout` is `120`\n177: - **WHEN** the request is built\n178: - **THEN** effective timeout SHALL be `120` and body SHALL contain `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: command string split into list\n181: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")`\n182: - **WHEN** the body is constructed\n183: - **THEN** `command` field SHALL be `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (split by whitespace)\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: non-zero exit code raises error\n186: - **GIVEN** response JSON is `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error\", \"stdout\": \"\"}`\n187: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n188: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\", command=\"ls\")` SHALL be raised\n189: \n190: ### Requirement: run_code\n191: The system SHALL write code to a timestamped file and execute it via the interpreter.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Python code execution\n194: - **GIVEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hi')\")`\n195: - **WHEN** the method executes\n196: - **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with a timestamped `.py` file, then `execute_command(\"python3 <file>\")`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: language alias normalization\n199: - **GIVEN** `language` is `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n200: - **WHEN** `run_code` executes\n201: - **THEN** it SHALL be treated as Python and follow the same path as `\"python\"`\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: write_file\n204: The system SHALL POST base64-encoded content to `api/files`.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: write file with base64 content\n207: - **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")`\n208: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n209: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64 of 'hello'>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n210: \n211: ### Requirement: upload_file\n212: The system SHALL POST multipart form data to `api/files` with session header.\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: multipart upload\n215: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(\"/local/file.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")`\n216: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n217: - **THEN** POST `api/files` with `files={'file': open('/local/file.txt', 'rb')}`, `data={'path': '/remote/path.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, and header `x-agentcube-session-id` explicitly set\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: download_file\n220: The system SHALL GET file content with streaming and write to local path.\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: streaming download\n223: - **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path.txt\", \"/local/out.txt\")`\n224: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n225: - **THEN** GET `api/files/remote/path.txt` (with `lstrip(\"/\")`), `stream=True`, and content SHALL be written in chunks to `/local/out.txt`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: clean path strips leading slash\n228: - **GIVEN** `remote_path = \"/absolute/path.txt\"`\n229: - **WHEN** download URL is constructed\n230: - **THEN** `clean_path` SHALL be `\"absolute/path.txt\"`\n231: \n232: ### Requirement: list_files\n233: The system SHALL GET file listing with path query parameter.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: list files in path\n236: - **GIVEN** `list_files(\"/some/path\")`\n237: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n238: - **THEN** GET `api/files?path=/some/path`\n239: \n240: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close\n241: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: close releases session\n244: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n245: - **WHEN** the method executes\n246: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructor\n253: The system SHALL initialize the agent runtime data plane client with invocation base URL.\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: base URL construction\n256: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"http://router:8080\", namespace=\"ns\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n257: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n258: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `\"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/ns/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER class constant\n261: - **GIVEN** the class definition\n262: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER` is accessed\n263: - **THEN** the value SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: bootstrap_session_id\n266: The system SHALL GET the invocation base URL and extract session ID from response header.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: session ID extracted from header\n269: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` returns response with header `x-agentcube-session-id: \"new-session\"`\n270: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"new-session\"`\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: missing session ID header raises error\n274: - **GIVEN** GET `{base_url}` response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id`\n275: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` executes\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n277: \n278: ### Requirement: invoke\n279: The system SHALL POST JSON payload to the invocation base URL with session header.\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: invoke with session header\n282: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s1\", payload={\"msg\": \"hello\"})`\n283: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n284: - **THEN** POST `{base_url}` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: s1` and `Content-Type: application/json`, body SHALL be JSON `{\"msg\": \"hello\"}`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: invoke with default timeout\n287: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=None)`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `self.timeout=120`\n288: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n289: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: invoke with custom timeout\n292: - **GIVEN** `invoke(\"s1\", payload, timeout=60.0)`\n293: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n294: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(5.0, 60.0)`\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: invoke without session_id raises error\n297: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty string\n298: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n299: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close\n302: The system SHALL release the underlying HTTP session.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: close releases session\n305: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called\n306: - **WHEN** the method executes\n307: - **THEN** `self.session.close()` SHALL be called\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ## Connection Pool Reuse\n312: \n313: ### Requirement: Session reuse within client\n314: The system SHALL reuse a single `requests.Session` instance per client for all HTTP operations.\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: same session for multiple requests\n317: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` calls `create_session` then `delete_session`\n318: - **WHEN** both requests are sent\n319: - **THEN** they SHALL use the same `self.session` instance\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: independent sessions across clients\n322: - **GIVEN** two `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` instances are created\n323: - **WHEN** their session objects are compared\n324: - **THEN** `client1.session` and `client2.session` SHALL be different objects\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Utility Functions\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: read_token_from_file\n331: The system SHALL read and strip token content from a file, returning empty string on missing file.\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: file exists with trailing newline\n334: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/token` contains `\"my-token\\n\"`\n335: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n336: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"`\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: file not found\n339: - **GIVEN** file `/tmp/nonexistent` does not exist\n340: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/nonexistent\")` is called\n341: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"\"`\n342: \n343: ### Requirement: get_logger\n344: The system SHALL create a named logger with configurable level.\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: logger with custom level\n347: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_module\", level=\"DEBUG\")`\n348: - **WHEN** the function executes\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL return a Logger named `\"test_module\"` with level `DEBUG`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Exception Hierarchy\n354: \n355: ### Requirement: Exception classes\n356: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n359: - **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=\"ls\")`\n360: - **WHEN** the exception is created\n361: - **THEN** `exc.exit_code` SHALL be `1`, `exc.stderr` SHALL be `\"err\"`, `exc.command` SHALL be `\"ls\"`, and `str(exc)` SHALL contain `\"Command failed (exit 1): err\"`\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: exception inheritance\n364: - **GIVEN** the exception classes are defined\n365: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n366: - **THEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL all be subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n\n(End of file - total 366 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the HTTP client layer of the AgentCube Python SDK — session creation with connection pooling, control plane and data plane HTTP client contracts, header management, timeout behavior, error handling, and utility functions.\n\n---\n\n## HTTP Session Factory\n\n### Requirement: create_session\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` function that returns a `requests.Session` configured with connection pooling.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880811141,"end":1775880811162}}}}
